<section xml:id="sec_N2LR" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The Rotational Law of Motion</title>
		
      <video youtube="JXxc0o1iAH4">      <description>An introduction to the rotational law of motion.</description></video>
    

	<definition xml:id="def_net-torque">
	<title>Net torque</title>
	<statement>
	<p>The <term>net torque</term> on an object or system is equal to the (vector) sum of all torques acting on it: <m>\vec{\tau}_{net} = \sum_i \vec{\tau}_i = \vec{\tau}_1 + \vec{\tau}_2 + \vec{\tau}_3 + \dots</m>.</p>
	</statement>
	</definition>

	<principle xml:id="law_N2LR">
	<title>The Rotational Law of Motion</title>
	<statement>
	<p>The net torque on an object or system is equivalent to the product of object's moment of inertia <m>I</m> and its angular acceleration <m>\alpha</m>: <m>\vec{\tau}_{net} = I\vec{\alpha}</m>.</p>
	</statement>
	</principle>


